{{SequenceUtil}} is what JIRA (via OfBiz) uses as ID sequence for new entities. The way it works is quite fragile and wasteful, in that every time the table storing sequences is manipulated outside of {{SequenceUtil}}, the current {{SequenceUtil}} has to be trashed by means of calling {{GenericDelegator.refereshSequencer}}. Because the sequence util uses in-memory ID banks of size 100, every time we refresh we lose anything from 0 to 100 IDs from the sequence. This could be improved by setting the sequence value in the DB table to the current in-memory sequence value upon {{refreshSequencer}} and when the {{GenericDelegator}} is shut down. Performance hit should be minimal

